items.abstract: <jats:p>This paper provides the results of research on temperature changes of cylindrical specimens depending on the pattern of the multiaxial load. The research were made by using passive infrared thermography. It was found out that the average temperature value is significantly dependent on the plastic strain energy and that the temperature change amplitude depends on the nominal normal stress (except for torsion).</jats:p>
